    <h4>Description:</h4>
    <p>Kadhi Chawal is a popular North Indian dish made with a yogurt-based gram flour curry and served with steamed rice. It's tangy, comforting, and often includes gram flour fritters (pakoras).</p>

    <h4>Prep Time:</h4>
    <p>‚è±Ô∏è <strong>30 minutes</strong></p>

    <h4>Ingredients:</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>1 cup yogurt (curd)</li>
        <li>2 tbsp besan (gram flour)</li>
        <li>2 cups water</li>
        <li>1 tsp mustard seeds</li>
        <li>1/2 tsp cumin seeds</li>
        <li>1/4 tsp turmeric powder</li>
        <li>1/2 tsp red chili powder</li>
        <li>Salt to taste</li>
        <li>1 tbsp oil</li>
        <li>Optional: fried pakoras (gram flour fritters)</li>
        <li>Cooked rice (for serving)</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Instructions:</h4>
    <ol>
        <li>In a bowl, whisk yogurt, besan, water, turmeric, red chili powder, and salt until smooth.</li>
        <li>Heat oil in a pan. Add mustard and cumin seeds and let them splutter.</li>
        <li>Pour in the yogurt mixture and stir continuously to avoid curdling.</li>
        <li>Simmer the kadhi for 20-25 minutes, stirring occasionally.</li>
        <li>Add fried pakoras if desired and cook for 5 more minutes.</li>
        <li>Serve hot with steamed rice.</li>
    </ol>
